{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"body":"Round-6 design convergence (escalation session): appended 'Producer-signing & compute-runtime design resolution' to the epic. Settled: fork A (uniform producer signing — gate producers mint rebar.opcert.v1 with the ambient env's Ed25519 key; trusted server is an ordinary pinned environment; double-signing dissolves); local key genesis <tracker>/.opcert-key; NO verify.opcert_env_id repo key (signer identity = deployment config; consumer policy = existing verify.require_environment/opcert_enforce_since; one new key verify.opcert_remote_url); per-kind native verdicts + transport-status/verdict split in the remote job API (LLMError -> status=error); runtime = ECS Fargate + API Gateway SigV4 + async job API (Lambda rejected: 15-min ceiling + sync timeout; shared review-bot VM rejected: key isolation — NB review_bot is actually compose-on-a-VM, not Fargate as the round-5 discussion assumed); server stateless + store-read-only (client persists the self-authenticating envelope). Re-decomposed: NEW story 8d8e (producer seam, expand) + NEW story 76d2 (AWS IaC + real deploy, authenticated CLI in scope); ee0b narrowed to the service+client; 8f1d narrowed to pure contract phase; 6a89 updated. Deps: ee0b->8d8e, 76d2->ee0b, 8f1d->8d8e."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783997981004734001,"uuid":"99295c68-97d1-4fcd-a5a5-eaa523096f5a"}